<h2>Welcome to Pacific Union School!</h2>

  <!-- This line closes the PHP if statement -->

<div class="entry">
<p><span style="color: #800080;"><span style="color: #000000;">Welcome to our web site! Please see the important information below, or check out our pages (right) for information.</span></span></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Here are some </span><a href="https://sites.google.com/pacificunionschool.org/pu-distance-learning/home">Student Resources</a> for your time away from school, and here is our <a href="http://odin.pacificunionschool.org/">“Campus Page”</a> of links to get to your old favorites.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Our Counseling staff is available to serve our families.  </strong>You can email Ana Gyenis-Iovi at <a href="mailto:agyenis-iovi@pacificunionschool.org">agyenis-iovi@pacificunionschool.org</a> to make an appointment for Tuesdays between 1:30 and 2:30pm, or email Tonja Speed at <a href="mailto:tspeed@pacificunionschool.org">tspeed@pacificunionschool.org</a> for an appointment on Thursdays between 11am-Noon.</p>
<p><strong>Humboldt-Del Norte SELPA is offering parent behavioral support</strong> Zoom sessions (free) for all parents and guardians. <a href="http://www.pacificunionschool.org/wp-content/uploads/Parent-Behavioral-Support-Flier.pdf">See the flyer here for information.</a></p>
<h1><span style="color: #800080;"><strong>COVID-19 Information </strong></span></h1>
<p><a href="http://www.pacificunionschool.org/wp-content/uploads/COVIDLetterApr2120.pdf"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="color: #993300;"><strong>Update-COVID19 and the rest of the School Year (April 20)</strong></span></span></a></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt; color: #993300;"><a style="color: #993300;" href="http://www.pacificunionschool.org/wp-content/uploads/school-closure-5-2.pdf"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Update – School Facilities Closure (April 2, 2020)</span></a></span></strong></p>
<p>.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="color: #993300; font-size: 12pt;"><a style="color: #993300;" href="http://www.pacificunionschool.org/wp-content/uploads/Letter3-19.pdf"><strong>Letter from Superintendent Rene McBride March 19 (Link)</strong></a></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><a href="http://www.pacificunionschool.org/wp-content/uploads/Letter3-19es.pdf"><strong><span class="tlid-translation translation" lang="es"><span class="" title=""><span style="color: #993300;">Carta del Superintendente Rene McBride 19 de marzo (Enlace)</span></span></span></strong></a></span></p>
<h2><span style="color: #800080;">Free Lunch Locations</span></h2>
<p>Dear Pacific Union Families,</p>
<p>We want to make sure kids in our district have access to lunches if they need them. Look for our school bus at the following locations and times Monday – Friday. We will be delivering free lunches to ANY child under 18 who may be in need of food, regardless of where they go to school.</p>
<p>We will continue to update you as often as possible. Thank you for your support and understanding.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">11:30 – 12:30 At School / En frente de la escuela</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">11:30 – 11:40 Valley East Blvd. @ Halen Drive</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">11:45 – 11:55 Boyd Road @ Courtyard Apartments</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">12:00 – 12:10 Boyd Road @ Town &amp;amp; Country Mobile Park</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">12:20 – 12:30 Bridge Parking Lot @ Mad River Rd.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">12:40 – 12:50 Alliance &amp;amp; 27th  St</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">12:55 – 1:05 Janes Rd. &amp;amp; Bay School Road</p>
<hr>
<p>Updated (as of 3-15-20) Press Release (English and Spanish) regarding School Closures due to COVID-19</p>
<p><a href="http://www.pacificunionschool.org/wp-content/uploads/PR-COVID-19-School-Closures.pdf"><span style="color: #800080;"><strong><span style="color: #993300;">HCOE School Closure Update 3-15-20</span></strong></span></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.pacificunionschool.org/wp-content/uploads/PR-COVID-19-School-Closures-Spanish.pdf"><strong><span style="color: #993300;">HCOE Actualizaciones de cierre de escuelas 3-15-20</span></strong></a></p>
<h2><span style="color: #800080;"><strong>Pacific Union School Closure.</strong></span></h2>
<p>(Sunday, March 15, 2020)</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dear Pacific Union Families, </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After speaking with County Superintendent Chris Hartley and Senator McGuire, Pacific Union School District has made the decision to temporarily close our school in response to the COVID-19 virus. This precaution is being taken to address the social distancing and recommendations by the state.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Staff is working on preparing enrichment packets that will be available to families beginning Wednesday, March 18th.  School will be closed through Friday, March 27th and we will evaluate then if we will reopen or remain closed. Please regularly check the school website, email, and text messages.  We will continue to update you as we are able to provide additional services and information.  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">As always, thank you for your continued support during this unprecedented time.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sincerely,</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rene L. McBride<br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Superintendent</span></p>
<p>—<br>
Estimadas familias de Pacific Union,</p>
<p>Después de hablar con el Superintendente del Condado ChrisHartley y el Senador McGuire, el DistritoEscolar Pacific Uniontomó la decisión de cerrar temporalmente nuestra escuela enrespuesta al virus COVID-19. Esta precaución se está tomandopara abordar el distanciamiento social y las recomendacionesdelestado.</p>
<p>El personal está trabajando en la preparación de paquetes deenriquecimiento que estarán disponibles paralas familias a partirdel miércoles 18 de marzo. La escuela estará cerrada hasta elviernes 27 de marzo y luegoevaluaremos si volveremos a abrir osi permaneceremos cerrados. Por favor revise regularmente elsitio webde la escuela, el correo electrónico y los mensajes detexto. Continuaremos actualizándolo a medida quepodamosbrindarle servicios e información adicionales.</p>
<p>Como siempre, gracias por su continuo apoyo durante estetiempo sin precedentes.</p>
<p>Sinceramente,<br>
Rene L. McBride<br>
Superintendente</p>
<hr>
<h4>(3-12-20) Pacific Union School District is closely monitoring the coronavirus (COVID-19) and any occurrences within Humboldt County and our surrounding communities.  Currently, there are no known or suspected cases of coronavirus within our District. However, we are taking action and coordinating efforts to help prevent the spread of any illnesses. These precautionary measures include the following:</h4>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
<li>School staff are taking extra time to carefully clean and sanitize school classrooms and common areas.</li>
</ul>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
<li>School staff are talking to students and reminding them of the importance of washing their hands often and to cover any cough/sneeze with a tissue or sleeve.</li>
</ul>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
<li>Parents and guardians are also encouraged to speak to students to reinforce proper hand washing and make sure they are washing their hands often.</li>
</ul>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
<li>If your student is sick, please keep them at home. Students should not return to school until a fever has been gone for at least 24 hours without the use of fever-reducing medicines.</li>
</ul>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
<li>Pacific Union School District will keep students/families informed of any developments through our notification systems and this website.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span style="color: #993300;">Información de COVID-19</span></h4>
<p><strong>El Distrito Escolar Pacific Union está monitoreando de cerca el coronavirus (COVID-19) y cualquier ocurrencia dentro del Condado de Humboldt y nuestras comunidades circundantes. Actualmente, no hay casos conocidos o sospechosos de coronavirus en nuestro Distrito. Sin embargo, estamos tomando medidas y coordinando esfuerzos para ayudar a prevenir la propagación de cualquier enfermedad. Estas medidas de precaución incluyen lo siguiente:</strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
<li>El personal escolar está tomando tiempo adicional para limpiar y desinfectar cuidadosamente las aulas escolares y las áreas comunes.</li>
<li>El personal de la escuela habla con los estudiantes y les recuerda la importancia de lavarse las manos con frecuencia y cubrirse la tos / estornudos con un pañuelo o una manga.</li>
<li>También se alienta a los padres y tutores a hablar con los estudiantes para reforzar el lavado de manos adecuado y asegurarse de que se laven las manos con frecuencia.</li>
<li>Si su estudiante está enfermo, manténgalo en casa. Los estudiantes no deben regresar a la escuela hasta que la fiebre haya desaparecido durante al menos 24 horas sin el uso de medicamentos antifebriles.</li>
<li>El Distrito Escolar Pacific Union mantendrá a los estudiantes / familias informados sobre cualquier desarrollo a través de nuestros sistemas de notificación y este sitio web.</li>
</ul>
